      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_MassDist_GetXMLMassDistributionTreeDataGroupByAgency",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to generate an XML representation of a mass distribution contact list, grouped by agency. It retrieves primary and secondary contact information associated with a given distribution profile ID, organizes them by agency divisions, and outputs the data in an XML format. This procedure is useful for applications that need to display or process contact information hierarchically grouped by agency."
        }
      ]
    },
